       <h1 style="text-align: center;">INVESTMENT CRITERIA </h1>

         <p1 style="margin-left: 30px;"><span1>Characteristics.</span1> We look for companies with proven business models, strong market potential, sustainable competitive advantages, and products or services that are disruptive to their industry -- companies that solve problems and satisfy demand through superior innovation, creativity, economics and execution.</p1>

         <p1 style="margin-left: 30px;"><span1>Size.</span1> We look for companies with EBITDA of $5-15 million or with an enterprise value of $20 to $100 million.</p1>

         <p1 style="margin-left: 30px;"><span1>Sectors.</span1> We invest in the sectors where our team has deep experience and has previously invested with success. Those sectors include aerospace, business services, consumer products, education, energy, entertainment, health, media, technology, and transportation.</p1>

         <p1 style="margin-left: 30px;"><span1>Location.</span1> We look for companies with a connection to Utah and the Mountain West, though we invest wherever we find the best opportunities.</p1>

         <p1 style="margin-left: 30px;"><span1>Amount.</span1> We look to invest a minimum of $5mm for a controlling interest in the voting shares of the company.</p1>

         <p1 style="margin-left: 30px;"><span1>Tenure.</span1> We typically hold our investments for a minimum of three years, actively working with management to execute our growth strategy until we accomplish a successful exit.</p1>

         <p1 style="margin-left: 30px; padding-bottom: 30px"><span1>Returns.</span1> We look for investments that we believe can reasonably achieve a minimum IRR of 25%.</p1>




